The paper deals with a nonlinear vector precoding scheme for wireless MIMO systems, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also uses the replica method, which is a statistical physics technique commonly used in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG) and the analysis applies to a very general class of MIMO channels, which could fall under the signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
